n":true},"contactCard":[{"service":"Mostly AMVs (YT)","value":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.youtube.com\u002F@goyavoyage","visibility":"public"},{"service":"Fanfics (AO3)","value":"https:\u002F\u002Farchiveofourown.org\u002Fusers\u002FGoyavoyage","visibility":"public"}],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null}},{"comment":{"commentId":"5b6ee45b-1644-4965-a8ec-1f9201f4d18b","postedAtISO":"2024-03-20T22:40:15.014Z","deleted":false,"body":"i _think_ I understand how it works conceptually but i do not get why it works with the spin animation (or why it works, if i'm being honest) lmao\nincredible job","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"6fc4069b-815d-4806-9686-60b62792a4d3","postedAtISO":"2024-03-22T23:54:13.878Z","deleted":false,"body":"there are a couple of posts that go over it in more detail ([tutorial: how to make cohost accept basically any animation you want](https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Foatmealine\u002Fpost\u002F303620-tutorial-how-to-mak) and [tutorial: cool custom animation tricks](https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Foatmealine\u002Fpost\u002F310029-tutorial-cool-custo) by @oatmealine and [CSS animation with `transform`ed `spin`s](https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Fionchy\u002Fpost\u002F2230465-css-animation-with) by @ionchy go over uses and [a post by](https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Fxenofem\u002Fpost\u002F2422190-read-way-too-many-w3) @xenofem goes over the reasoning behind it)\n\nbut in short,\nalone, the spin animation needs to rotate the element from 0 (an **implicit** start value) to 360 (an **explicit** end value) degrees\nto know the rotation at a specific time, it can interpolate between those two **values**\n\nwhen you add a non rotation transformation with `transform`, say a translation,\nyou're telling the element to translate first\n(the 0 rotation isn't explicitly mentioned in the definition of the spin animation)\nthe spin animation's final transform wants it to rotate first\nbut you can't interpolate between the **values** of a translation and a rotation\n(what's halfway between 5 em and 3 radians?)\nso the rest of the transformations are put into equivalent transformation matrices, which can be interpolated between\n\nthe problem is that a 360 degree rotation is equivalent to no rotation at all\n\nsay you have a clock sitting on the floor\nthe clock's hour hand rotates 360 degrees every 12 hours\nfrom midnight to noon, you know that it **should** rotate 360 degrees\nbut if you take a picture of it at midnight\nthen another one at noon\nyou see that both of the pictures are identical\nthe hour hand might as well not have moved at all\n\na transformation matrix tells you how something differs from an initial state\nbut something that has undergone a 360 degree rotation doesn't look different to something that hasn't moved at all\n\nin the end, the only transformations that are shown are the ones you added\nsince the element is essentially being told to go from a 0 degree rotation to a 0 degree rotation\n\nbut all of this is happening because the 0 degree rotation is implicit\nif you add an explicit 0 degree rotation before your other transformations, the spin is visible again\nand your other transformations are also interpolated using their values\nif you don't want the spin, you can set the initial rotation to 360 degrees\n\nah\nthat was less short than intended\nin pant\n","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"b92c51df-8663-4986-877f-e8770db48fbb","postedAtISO":"2024-03-22T23:56:46.704Z","deleted":false,"body":"omg thank you for the write-up!! (Im sure other ppl would love to see it so if you post it on its own i'm gonna repost the shit out of it)","children":[],"postId":5190213,"inReplyTo":"6fc4069b-815d-4806-9686-60b62792a4d3","hasCohostPlus":true,"hidden":false},"canInteract":"allowed","canEdit":"not-allowed","canHide":"not-allowed","poster":{"projectId":291,"handle":"eramdam","displayName":"Damien","dek":"\"You're obviously the Grungler\"","description":"cis; 30s; Web dev; videos gamer; enjoyer of music