- --></a> goes over the reasoning behind it)<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>but in short,<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->alone, the spin animation needs to rotate the element from 0 (an <!-- --><strong>implicit<!-- --></strong> start value) to 360 (an <!-- --><strong>explicit<!-- --></strong> end value) degrees<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->to know the rotation at a specific time, it can interpolate between those two <!-- --><strong>values<!-- --></strong></p>
<!-- --><p>when you add a non rotation transformation with <!-- --><code>transform<!-- --></code>, say a translation,<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->you&#x27;re telling the element to translate first<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->(the 0 rotation isn&#x27;t explicitly mentioned in the definition of the spin animation)<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->the spin animation&#x27;s final transform wants it to rotate first<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->but you can&#x27;t interpolate between the <!-- --><strong>values<!-- --></strong> of a translation and a rotation<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->(what&#x27;s halfway between 5 em and 3 radians?)<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->so the rest of the transformations are put into equivalent transformation matrices, which can be interpolated between<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>the problem is that a 360 degree rotation is equivalent to no rotation at all<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>say you have a clock sitting on the floor<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->the clock&#x27;s hour hand rotates 360 degrees every 12 hours<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->from midnight to noon, you know that it <!-- --><strong>should<!-- --></strong> rotate 360 degrees<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->but if you take a picture of it at midnight<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->then another one at noon<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->you see that both of the pictures are identical<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->the hour hand might as well not have moved at all<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>a transformation matrix tells you how something differs from an initial state<!-- --><br/>
<!-- -->but something that has undergone a 360 degree rotation doesn&#x27;t look different to something that hasn&#x27;t moved at all<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>in the end, the only transformations that are shown are the ones you added<!-- --><br/>
